It is observed that an increasing ISC-time leads to attenuating crystal orientation. The ISC-8 and 12 s samples show discrete Bragg scattering spots (or arcs) from {111} and {202} facets, indicative of oriented quasi-2D phases. In contrast, the crystals in ISC-15s, 22 s, and 30 s samples are randomly packed with powder-like diffraction rings. All the samples feature (0k0) peaks at low-q region, suggesting the existence of mixed low-n phases. In order to quantitatively analyze the texture, the (1¯11¯)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
